RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 62. Claiming Purse 12500. (PLUS UP TO $625 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHEZA HUNK well reserved off the leaders to the top of the lane, commenced a rally from the rail, angled out to the five path to split horses late in the lane, made the front in final seventy yards, leaned out into the runner- up in the late stages and prevailed. RECLAIMED tracked pace, made a steady advance through the turn, loomed boldly inside the sixteenth pole, was bumped by the winner several times late in the drive and just missed. KAYLEE'S SHADOW was well behind in the early going, circled eight wide at the head of the stretch and closed with a belated rush to be going best of all at the wire in a good effort. LET FREEDOM BLING broke alertly and settled to a stalking position, moved up to duel for the lead through the turn, briefly took the lead in upper stretch and was out-kicked late. MISS CARMEN rushed up along the fence to duel on the lead, battled gamely to the quarter pole and gave way. SATIN HEART stalked the pace from between horses top of the lane and weakened in the drive. LUMBERJACK LESLIE went evenly as no threat. ABIGAIL ALDEN flashed brief speed and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 5F Turf CR: 86. Allowance Purse 33500. (PLUS UP TO $6,700 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TEXAS BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 5, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since November 5, 2022 Allowed 4 lbs. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRUCELEA chased the pace from the inside, was gaining gamely on the turn to edge clear in the early stretch and held on well till the end. SEIZE THE TREASURE chased the pace while five wide into the turn, then angled in to the two path in the early stretch to rally and was closing willingly in the end. MY GOLDEN M was in a hard drive to vie for the lead from the inside, continued to bid gamely in the stretch but was out finished in the end and was best for show. IRISH EXPECTATIONS raced behind rivals along the inside until the early stretch then rallied in deep stretch but it was too little too late. MORE LIKE IT settled along the inside into the turn, then angled out five wide in the early stretch to rally and was closing well in the end. MISTER CHAIRMAN vied for the lead while two wide, continued to bid gamely throughout the turn, then gave way in the stretch. JR'S PACIFICO chased the pace while four wide, then dropped back on the turn, re bid in the stretch but came up empty. GUERO DINERO vied for the lead while three deep, was in tight then checked on the turn, then flattened out in the stretch. HE'S A BOMB vied for the lead while four wide, was in a hard drive throughout the turn, was used up and gave way in the end. CHAMPAGNE STOOPER trailed throughout and was no factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GREATEST GLORY was moving up along the inside to take command at the five furlong marker, cleared the turn, and was kept to task till the end. SHEZA CAT veered in at the start, then was unhurried early, was moving up along then inside on the turn, came out three wide in the early stretch, dug in gamely and continued to close well. SIMPERING SMILE raced in the middle of the field while three wide, then made a mild bid on the turn and found more in the stretch to close well for the show prize. HIT'EM UP chased the pace along the inside down the backstretch and throughout the turn under a steady drive and needed more in the end. QUEEN OF MAGNOLIA was bumped on both sides at the start, was unhurried early along the inside, then came out four wide in the upper stretch bid down the lane but it was too little too late. ATTA MOY GIRL bid for the lead while four wide, then pressed the pace down the late backstretch and into the turn while two wide, was used up and tired in the stretch. BLONDES HAVEMO FUN was away from the gate quickly to lead the way down the early backstretch, then gradually faded throughout and had no final bid in the end.

BLING BLING BLING bumped rival at the start, tracked the pacesetters to the quarter pole, rallied strongly in the lane to be gaining late. ZAVALA bumped leaving the stall, raced up the rail to press the pace for a half mile and flattened out. RODEO CHAMP trailed early, launched a wide bid into the turn and finished evenly. CRAFTY CHARLIE settled along the inside down the backstretch, then came out four wide to bid on the turn and into the stretch and was no threat. JJ'S AMERICAN DIVA bumped foe at the start, then vied for the lead while two wide, then faded heading into the turn and had no final bid in the stretch. RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 7 7F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 13500. (PLUS UP TO $2,700 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JANUARY 1, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COSTANARMANDALEG broke alertly to press the pace from three wide through the turn, battled in the lane between horses while exchanging bumps with CARLOS LOVES TEE leaving the sixteenth pole, fought from between horses to the wire bumping with the runner-up in the final strides and finished determinedly to get the nod. NORA'S LEGACY dueled from between horses early to take a short lead down the backstretch, fought from the rail in a three horse duel at the head of the stretch, took the lead in the late stages, shied away from the winner fifty yards from the finish briefly tossing his head, dug back in, bumped winner late and just missed. CARLOS LOVES TEE broke outward leaving the gate, dropped into a stalking position down the backside, rallied three wide to take the lead at the head of the lane, drifted in bumping the winner and hung in the late stages. GRAN MANNA moved up the rail leaving the chute to press the pace from the rail, checked by rider in the turn while trying to get out, raced wide while failing to gain from there on. MAYAPRETTY trailed the field to the top of the lane and showed late interest gaining ground down the stretch. SIMPLE PLEASURE was well placed early on and made a mild bid down the lane while never posing a threat. SHESMYBROKER dropped back during the run down the backside and was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 8 1M Turf CR: 86. Claiming Purse 19000. (PLUS UP TO $3,800 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $30,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: READY TO ROLL was well rated while two wide on the backstretch and into the far turn then rallied in the early stretch, dueled with an inner rival in the final furlong and was up just in time to prevail. GOLD VERMILION chased the pace from the inside down the backstretch and into the far turn, gained the lead in the upper stretch, then dueled with an outer foe in deep stretch and was out finished in the end by a neck. VETERAN'S HOLIDAY raced in the back of the field while three wide, was moving up to bid from the inside on the far turn, angled out to the four path in the stretch to close willingly in the end. RESOLUTIONIST settled while three wide, was gaining ground on the far turn from the five path then closed well in the stretch. HOURGLASS FIGURE raced from the inside in the middle of the field from the first turn into the second turn, then rallied in the early stretch but came up evenly in the end. JOHN DOUGH raced in the middle of the field while two wide, then settled back down the backstretch, came out six wide to rally in the upper stretch but it was too little too late. SHAMAYIM was under a steady drive while racing from the three path down the backstretch, was urging on the far turn to rally from the five path in the stretch but came up empty in the end. MERCI set the pace along the inside, was in a long drive then faltered in the home stretch. DARE TO BE WILD raced at an even pace while three wide down the backstretch and throughout the far turn then flattened out in the stretch. TAPIT CITY settled behind the field along the inside then made a mild bid on the far turn and was no threat. ENDLESS SUNSET settled along the inside throughout the first three quarters then bid from the two path in the stretch and was no menace.
